{
  "texts": [
    "They utilised AI tools to personalise feedback and provide specific examples.",
    "When conveying feedback, they maximised the benefits of faceto-face interactions, incorporated visual aids and diagrams, and often complemented written feedback with spoken language.",
    "On the issue of what constituted personalised feedback, our participants emphasised that it should be individualised and tailored for a specific student's needs, be clear on ways to improve, be actionable, accurate and constructive, and above all timely.",
    "This finding echoed Hyland and Hyland (2019).",
    "Our participants suggested integrating AI tools in higher education has offered possibilities for enhancing the delivery of personalised feedback, particularly for NESB educators."
  ]
}